Investigation into Remains of Korean Draftees Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tokyo, October 5 (KNS-KCNA) -- Hong Sang Jin, secretary general of the Central Headquarters of the Koreans' Side to the Group for Investigation into Truth behind Korean Victims of Forcible Drafting, and Akihiro Harada, director of the Central Headquarters of the Japanese' Side to the group, and representatives of the Japanese' sides in Tokyo, Kanagawa, Chiba, Saitama, Tochigi and Fukushima to the group strongly urged the Japanese government to actively come out in the investigation into the remains of Korean victims of forcible drafting.
 They jointly called a press conference in Tokyo on Oct. 3 at which they referred to the fact that on Sept. 28 the Japanese government made public the results of the investigation which claim that the remains of only 868 Korean draftees have been confirmed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Even non-governmental probe put the estimated number of the Korean victims of the forcible drafting at 50,000 at minimum, they noted, adding that the government's investigation is too insufficient. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They accused the Japanese government of refusing under unreasonable reason to meet the request made to the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare by the group last August to start the "investigation into Korean employees." By this work style it is hard to expect any progress in the investigation, they said, urging the authorities to boldly open the necessary information to the public. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed a report on investigation conducted in different parts of the Kanto area.

WPK Birthday Celebrated in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held in Bridgetown, Barbados, and Ulan Bator, Mongolia, round-table talks and film show at the building of the Misr Arab Socialist Party, photo exhibition and film show in Tashkent, Uzbekistan, from Sept. 26 to 29 on the occasion of the 60th founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 On display at the photo exhibition were photos introducing revolutionary battle sites in the area of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants of the film shows watched Korean film "Military and Civilian Parade Celebrating the 55th Founding Anniversary of the Glorious WPK." 
 The chairman of the Barbadian preparatory committee to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the WPK in his speech at the meeting said that the WPK has grown strong to be a revolutionary party in the era of Juche and it has achieved great successes in the revolution and construction despite all hardships under the leadership of General Secretary Kim Jong Il over the last 40 odd years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the Korean people are now making energetic efforts to achieve national reunification under the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration, he said the U.S. should not chill the ardent enthusiasm of the Korean people for reunification but do anything helpful to Korea's reunification. The Barbadian people fully support Korea's reunification by federal formula and will send firm solidarity to their just struggle, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of Kim Jong Suk Kindergarten in Ulan Bator said at the meeting that the children of the kindergarten and their parents know well about the three generals of Mt. Paektu who devoted themselves to the country and the people and widely introduce them to the Mongolian people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Misr Arab Socialist Party at the round-table talks stressed that the Korean people have stood firm against the arbitrary practices of the U.S. as they have Kim Jong Il at the top post of the WPK.

Pyongyang Electric Appliances Joint Venture Company Commissioned 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- The Pyongyang electric Appliances Joint Venture Company was commissioned Thursday.
 The company is a joint venture of the DPRK Card Watt-hour Meter Assembling Factory and the Chinese Beijing Fu Xing Xiao Cheng Electronic Technology Stock Co., Ltd. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will produce card watt-hour meters needed for scientifically controlling the consumption of electricity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The production of this type of meters will contribute to the development of national economy as they will help factories, enterprises and families make a rational use of electricity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day, Ju Tong Il, minister of Electricity and Coal Industries, and other officials and members of the Chinese company delegation headed by its General Manager Cheng Yi went round the production processes and products of the company, exchanging conversation about the need to methodically manage the company and intensify the work to increase the production in conformity with the daily expanding DPRK-China friendly relations.

Military Attache of Egyptian Embassy Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- Military Attache Mahmoud Mohamed Osman Atik of the Egyptian embassy here Thursday evening hosted a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on the occasion of the Egyptian army day.
 Present on invitation were Kim Sang Ik, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, generals and officers of the Korean People's Army, officials concerned, foreign diplomatic envoys and military attaches of foreign embassies and representatives of international organizations here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Egyptian Ambassador to the DPRK Moustafa Mohamed Ahmed Al Hateer and staff members of the Egyptian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the reception.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from European Internet Seminar
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, received a letter from the participants in the European Regional Internet Seminar on Songun Politics held from Sept. 23 to 25.
 The letter noted that the Songun idea of Korea established by President Kim Il Sung in his early years is being successfully carried forward by the energetic leadership of Kim Jong Il, another great general. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar was a very significant occasion which brought the greatness of the idea of the Songun politics and the validity of practical method and Kim Jong Il's great personality home to us and convinced us that under his outstanding leadership the Songun politics of Korea would surely emerge victorious, the letter said, and went on:
 The progressive humankind is convinced that it is only the Songun politics of Korea strengthening self-reliant national defence, defending the country's security and building people's socialism to defend the peace and stability of humankind and guarantee happiness of future in this world where destruction and massacre by a war forced by imperialism are prevalent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the Songun politics, Korea could defend its sovereignty and revolutionary gains and is now greeting in a bright prospect of building a great prosperous powerful nation despite all the offensives of political, economic, cultural and diplomatic pressure and military threat by the imperialist aligned forces against socialism.
 Some time ago we visited Korea on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of Korea's liberation and toured Mt. Paektu, the cradle of Songun politics where President Kim Il Sung and anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk left their sacred traces and Kim Jong Il was born and grew up to be a great man. Witnessing the victorious reality of Korea growing strong with the Songun politics, we renewed our target of life to be ardent advocates of  Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As there is Kim Jong Il, there is the great truth of Songun which will make the world prosperous and humankind happy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We, aspiring after justice, progress, independence, peace and friendship, will widely disseminate the greatness and invincible might of the Songun politics of Korea all over the world and activate the solidarity movement for supporting the just struggle of the Korean people to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and achieve national reunification for the sake of a peaceful and prosperous new world of future.

Rodong Sinmun on WPK's Cause of National Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- The Workers' Party of Korea has covered the victorious course of the cause of national reunification, invariably holding high the banner of independence symbolic of victory and dignity, which is shining as the undying feats in the national history. Rodong Sinmun says this in a signed article today.
 Over the last six decades the WPK has struggled, holding fast to the Juche idea as the ideological and theoretical, strategic and tactical guidelines for national reunification, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung pioneered and led the Korean revolution under the banner of Juche and had firmly maintained the principle of independence, putting it forward as supreme uncompromising one in the whole historical period of his leadership over the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The idea of national reunification put forward and consistently maintained by him is the steadfast idea of national independence, the idea of independent reunification on settling the issue of national reunification by the Korean nation itself with the stand of a master in accordance with its will and interests free from the interference of any foreign forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three principles of national reunification--independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity--, the ten-point programme for the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo set out by him are the most just and realistic great programme of reunification which is consistent with the steadfast idea of independent reunification and reflect the aspiration and will of the whole Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These three charters of national reunification are now shining as the highly important guidelines of independent reunification in the struggle for reunification.
 The cause of national reunification which started with independence and has won with independence has been put on a new high historical stage as it is advancing under the banner of "By our nation itself", the ideal of independence in the Songun era laid down by the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il ushered in a new era of independent reunification, holding high the banner of Songun at the time when the country was undergoing the grimmest ordeals. The banner of Songun Kim Jong Il held higher following the President's idea and tradition of Songun is the most steadfast banner of independence, the banner of patriotism leading the cause of national reunification to victory.
 The Songun idea which clarifies the Juche-oriented philosophy of arms, the principle of arms has provided a sure guarantee for winning victory in the acute showdown of strength, the showdown of arms with the anti-reunification forces and accomplishing the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pyongyang meeting and the adoption of the June 15 joint declaration were historic events of the nation produced by the Songun politics consistent with the principle of national independence, patriotic spirit and the WPK's policy of national reunification based on it and its initiative efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics of the WPK which has brought the era of "By our nation itself" serves as the treasured sword of independent reunification which provides a sure guarantee for its victorious advance.

